# 6. ぶつかり合う覚悟

Nene: So, you saw everything? Including that conversation just now?
Len: <Yeah... Sorry, I didn't mean to peek.>
Nene: No, that's okay. I'm actually glad you're here. I'm having trouble digesting what happened.
Nene: I do think I was in the wrong back there.
Nene: I didn't actually take Imura's feelings into consideration.
Nene: Ever since coming here, I feel like my emotions have been all over the place...
Len: <Huh?>
Nene: I've been telling myself to do my absolute best in order to keep growing as an actress...
Nene: But everyone here... They're all competing too hard against each other...
Nene: Also, they seem to have no trouble ignoring anyone in need or pain.
Nene: I know that auditions can be tough, but this feels...
Len: <I know what you mean. You're supposed to be putting on this show together, so it feels bad that things are like this...>
Len: <But, is that really...>
???: Kusanagi.
Nene: Byakkomachi!
Byakkomachi: Are you by yourself? I thought I heard someone else's voice just now...
Nene: Oh, no... I'm alone. Anyway, is something the matter?
Byakkomachi: I just ran into Imura.
Nene: ...!
Byakkomachi: I noticed her crying, so I decided to ask how she was doing. Then, she replied, “I said something really terrible to Kusanagi just now.”
Byakkomachi: She wants to apologize to you, but she's having trouble getting her thoughts together. So, I offered to relay her message to you.
Nene: Oh... I see...
Nene: Thank you, Byakkomachi.
Byakkomachi: There's no need to thank me.
Byakkomachi: But there is something I need to tell you, Kusanagi.
Nene: Huh...?
Byakkomachi: You still seem to be misunderstanding something.
Nene: What do you mean...? Misunderstanding...?
Byakkomachi: I imagine that you tried to cheer up Imura because you and her are both chasing after the same dream.
Byakkomachi: However, no one here at Morinomiya thinks like that.
Byakkomachi: Rather, we actively refuse to think like that.
Nene: ...!
Byakkomachi: Everyone here is striving to make their dream come true by becoming the best performer ever.
Byakkomachi: Because we all know that, we have no trouble throwing everything we have at each other when push comes to shove.
Byakkomachi: There is no room for pity. Rather...
Byakkomachi: Showing pity to your opponent would be inappropriate. This is a serious competition.
Byakkomachi: If you have the time to feel bad, then you have time to further polish your acting. If you succeed where others have failed, you owe them that much.
Nene: Oh...
Nene: (Right. I'm here to...)
Byakkomachi: If you disagree with that philosophy, then it would be best if you left this place immediately.
Nene: ...
Byakkomachi: That's all.
Len: <Nene...? Are you feeling okay...?>
Nene: *Nod*
Nene: I think I finally understand, after what Byakkomachi told me.
Nene: I realize now that I wasn't fully committing myself.
Nene: I came in intending to grow as an actress. But...
Nene: I framed it as taking the experience they could give me, and learning what they had to teach me. Deep down, I approached it passively...
Nene: I wasn't resolved to fight for and win this role like my life depended on it.
Nene: Which is why I kept hesitating... I kept looking around at others...
Nene: But no one here at Morinomiya thinks that way.
Nene: They're throwing absolutely everything they have at each other in order to become the best actors they can. In order to win.
Len: <Nene...>
Len: <I think your kindness and how you look out for those around you are really wonderful, Nene.>
Len: <But when push really comes to shove, I think there's something you have to prioritize more.>
Nene: Yeah...
Nene: And I'm glad I get that now...
Nene: So, I'm done looking around at everyone else.
Nene: I'm going to stand up straight and meet everyone else head-on.
Len: <Yeah. Break a leg!>
Nene: Thanks.
Nene: When I set out into the world, I'm probably gonna find myself clashing with others in much the same way.
Nene: So, I'm diving in head first...!!
Nene: “Ah, Louise! For you, I am willing to do anything. My life is yours!”
Nene: (No... This still doesn't feel right.)
Nene: (In this scene, Luca's...)
Nene: (His words sound gallant, but he's definitely feeling a complex mix of emotions.)
Nene: (He didn't want to hurt anyone. But there's no turning back now. He has to keep moving forward. Which is why...)
Nene: “Ah... Louise! For you, I am willing to do anything. My life is yours!”
Nene: *Nod* That's a bit better.
Nene: Alright, next...
Nene: Hey, are you guys free right now?!
Tsukasa: Hm? How can we help you, Nene?
Nene: It's about the character I'm auditioning for right now. I'm having some trouble with his character arc during the second half, so I'd love to hear what you guys think.
Rui: Oh, in that case, I'm all ears. What's causing your trouble?
Emu: Me too! I wanna help!
Nene: Umm... The part where Luca's named a deputy commander onwards.
Nene: “My charge is clear.”
Nene: “I, Luca Roussel, shall cleanse this land of every last treasonous rebel.”
Tsukasa: Hmm... You've definitely improved compared to when you first started, but I feel that you can do better than that, Nene.
Len: *Nod* I agree!
Rui: This is the scene that heralds Luca's descent into tyranny.
Rui: It's vital to convey to the audience that the timid boy has taken the first step on a path that ends with him as a complete monster. But how best to do that...
Nene: Right...
Nene: Oh, what if I used my eyes more...?
Len: Your eyes?
Nene: Yeah, by glowering a bit more... Like this.
Emu: Oh wow! You seem determined to complete your mission no matter what!
Nene: Good. I'll try going with this.
Nene: He sings the final song while taking his last breath in Louise's arms.
Nene: Singing while on my side is really hard, so I need to find a solid position and...
Nene: ♪——————...
Nene: No... My voice is going to sound funny if act too emotional.
Nene: Wait, I know... I can try that thing Ms. Kazamatsuri taught me.
